 {"id":"bd-2wpn0","title":"add mounted-path btrfs FIEMAP directory-fd EISDIR coverage","description":"Survey finding: btrfs mounted-path FIEMAP coverage currently proves regular-file reporting and edge cases, but the public refusal contract for directory fds is not frozen even though ffs-core returns IsDirectory/EISDIR. Scope: add a btrfs mounted-path ioctl probe against a directory fd that asserts exact EISDIR when the ioctl reaches FrankenFS userspace, with explicit soft-skip handling if the kernel/FUSE transport returns EOPNOTSUPP before dispatch. Acceptance: fuse_e2e freezes btrfs directory-fd FIEMAP refusal separately from transport-layer skips.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-21T09:11:19.834296614Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-21T21:47:23.683576611Z","closed_at":"2026-04-21T21:47:23.681729694Z","close_reason":"Completed","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
